1
00:00:02,900 --> 00:00:05,580
Where'd I put the charger again?

2
00:00:13,750 --> 00:00:15,350
Here.

3
00:00:15,350 --> 00:00:16,960
Thanks.

4
00:00:25,940 --> 00:00:31,010
<i>Things have changed slightly between us
ever since that day,</i>

5
00:00:31,010 --> 00:00:32,590
<i>a few months ago.</i>
[2 Months Ago]

6
00:00:32,590 --> 00:00:34,190
- Well...
- Well...

7
00:00:36,640 --> 00:00:38,170
You first.

8
00:00:38,960 --> 00:00:40,800
No, go ahead.

9
00:00:43,540 --> 00:00:45,050
I'm sorry.

10
00:00:46,850 --> 00:00:49,000
I was overly harsh with you.

11
00:00:49,000 --> 00:00:51,430
Call it a slip of the tongue.

12
00:00:53,230 --> 00:00:56,990
I... told you to do what you wanted?

13
00:00:59,490 --> 00:01:01,490
Oh, right.

14
00:01:01,490 --> 00:01:04,410
It's fine, I wasn't bothered by that at all.

15
00:01:04,410 --> 00:01:06,820
- At all?
- At all.

16
00:01:07,590 --> 00:01:09,690
I see...

17
00:01:09,690 --> 00:01:11,090
Yup.

18
00:01:12,430 --> 00:01:15,090
- Haru...
- I must've put you on the spot.

19
00:01:15,090 --> 00:01:17,090
I promise I won't ask again.

20
00:01:17,090 --> 00:01:18,260
Huh?

21
00:01:18,260 --> 00:01:22,050
Sorry I raised such a fuss about it.

22
00:01:31,230 --> 00:01:33,560
See you later.

23
00:01:33,560 --> 00:01:35,160
Take care.

24
00:01:40,300 --> 00:01:44,550
Say, are you free this weekend?

25
00:01:45,210 --> 00:01:47,040
- Huh?
- I mean...

26
00:01:47,040 --> 00:01:50,150
The two of us don't really go out together.

27
00:01:50,150 --> 00:01:53,170
Actually, if we exclude lunches and dinners,

28
00:01:53,170 --> 00:01:56,050
our outings together total to zero.

29
00:01:56,900 --> 00:02:00,420
You make a point.

30
00:02:00,420 --> 00:02:02,740
So let's change that.

31
00:02:05,220 --> 00:02:08,000
Or did you have plans?

32
00:02:08,900 --> 00:02:12,050
I don't. This is so exciting!

33
00:02:12,050 --> 00:02:14,000
Think of where you want to go, okay?

34
00:02:14,000 --> 00:02:15,450
I will.

35
00:02:19,490 --> 00:02:24,970
<i>Our relationship has changed,
ever so slightly.</i>

36
00:03:22,170 --> 00:03:26,280
[Episode 9]

37
00:03:28,130 --> 00:03:31,750
Hey there, Sensei.

38
00:03:31,750 --> 00:03:34,830
- Don't call me that.
- Why not?

39
00:03:34,830 --> 00:03:37,570
- You're releasing a book.
- Who would've thought, right?

40
00:03:37,570 --> 00:03:42,000
A short story I posted online went viral,

41
00:03:42,000 --> 00:03:44,720
and now it's going to be published.

42
00:03:44,720 --> 00:03:47,560
That just proves how popular it became.

43
00:03:47,560 --> 00:03:50,940
I suppose people enjoy risqué stories.

44
00:03:50,940 --> 00:03:53,940
I mean, a one-night stand
with a male prostitute?

45
00:03:53,940 --> 00:03:56,890
Now how'd you come up with that idea?

46
00:03:58,300 --> 00:04:04,240
Erm, well... rather than come up with it...

47
00:04:04,240 --> 00:04:08,350
I based the story off a friend of a friend.

48
00:04:08,350 --> 00:04:10,990
Fascinating.

49
00:04:15,410 --> 00:04:19,340
I'm that "friend", right?

50
00:04:19,340 --> 00:04:20,870
You can't deny it.

51
00:04:20,870 --> 00:04:23,400
Sorry.

52
00:04:23,400 --> 00:04:26,040
To think you'd become a published author.

53
00:04:26,040 --> 00:04:27,480
Your story reached 4.5 million views, right?

54
00:04:27,480 --> 00:04:29,470
I was just as shocked.

55
00:04:29,470 --> 00:04:33,950
I didn't realize my experience
would be such a hit sensation.

56
00:04:33,950 --> 00:04:36,430
Which you couldn't own up to,
so you pinned it on a "friend".

57
00:04:36,430 --> 00:04:37,800
Of course I couldn't!

58
00:04:37,800 --> 00:04:41,750
How could I admit I almost had sex
with a male therapy-prostitute?

59
00:04:41,750 --> 00:04:43,140
I see your point.

60
00:04:43,140 --> 00:04:44,810
His name was Natsuo, right?

61
00:04:44,810 --> 00:04:47,450
- Have you seen him since?
- No. I don't even know his number.

62
00:04:47,450 --> 00:04:52,120
Don't you want to use
the condoms he gave you?

63
00:04:52,120 --> 00:04:57,100
Well, I know I made a huge fuss about it,

64
00:04:57,100 --> 00:05:00,860
but things are going well between Ouji and I.

65
00:05:01,440 --> 00:05:03,800
Sure, we aren't intimate.

66
00:05:03,800 --> 00:05:06,620
But I really don't mind.

67
00:05:07,250 --> 00:05:10,640
I guess I just needed to release
my pent up sexual frustration.

68
00:05:10,640 --> 00:05:13,880
Hasn't Ouji noticed a change?

69
00:05:13,880 --> 00:05:18,810
He probably knows something happened.

70
00:05:18,810 --> 00:05:20,850
He hasn't seen your story circulating around?

71
00:05:20,850 --> 00:05:23,020
No! If he saw, it'd be over.

72
00:05:23,020 --> 00:05:24,790
Thank god I posted it anonymously.

73
00:05:24,790 --> 00:05:27,840
Won't your name be published
when it becomes a book?

74
00:05:27,840 --> 00:05:30,170
I haven't even told him I'm an author.

75
00:05:30,170 --> 00:05:34,280
So many secrets,
yet you say things are "going well".

76
00:05:34,280 --> 00:05:36,910
I mean...

77
00:05:37,560 --> 00:05:42,650
I think these secrets are actually helping.

78
00:05:43,870 --> 00:05:46,910
Ouji seems like a secretive guy, right?

79
00:05:46,910 --> 00:05:50,130
I suppose.

80
00:05:50,130 --> 00:05:53,370
While I'm the complete opposite of that.

81
00:05:53,370 --> 00:05:55,380
You certainly are.

82
00:05:56,480 --> 00:06:03,110
So now that I'm hiding something,
he seems bothered by it.

83
00:06:03,110 --> 00:06:06,250
What a roundabout way
of grabbing his attention.

84
00:06:06,250 --> 00:06:08,740
I wasn't trying to get his attention.

85
00:06:08,740 --> 00:06:10,900
It just happened as a result.

86
00:06:10,900 --> 00:06:14,060
Retreating as an offensive move, I see.

87
00:06:14,060 --> 00:06:15,060
"Move"?

88
00:06:15,060 --> 00:06:18,360
It's nothing that tactical, really.

89
00:06:18,360 --> 00:06:20,610
Should I give it a try?

90
00:06:20,610 --> 00:06:22,690
It's not that I wanted to retreat.

91
00:06:22,690 --> 00:06:25,980
But I can't retreat, as the customer.

92
00:06:25,980 --> 00:06:28,240
Sorry, what are we talking about?

93
00:06:28,240 --> 00:06:30,850
Me, of course.

94
00:06:30,850 --> 00:06:35,010
There's no point in retreating
when I need to pay to see him.

95
00:06:35,010 --> 00:06:37,720
Can't you ask to meet outside his shift?

96
00:06:37,720 --> 00:06:39,380
I wish I could.

97
00:06:39,380 --> 00:06:43,330
But that's rude to ask of a professional.

98
00:06:43,330 --> 00:06:45,230
How complex.

99
00:06:45,230 --> 00:06:47,470
Anyway, since I'd rather not try my luck,

100
00:06:47,470 --> 00:06:50,540
I'll just cough up the money, and push.

101
00:06:50,540 --> 00:06:53,360
I can only say, "good luck".

102
00:06:53,360 --> 00:06:57,540
What about you, Fuyumi?
Getting that youthful essence?

103
00:06:59,460 --> 00:07:01,050
Really, "essence"?

104
00:07:01,050 --> 00:07:03,730
I was trying to be less direct about it.

105
00:07:03,730 --> 00:07:05,310
Well, it didn't work.

106
00:07:05,310 --> 00:07:07,360
So, how are things going with him?

107
00:07:08,800 --> 00:07:10,610
[Hidamari Women's Clinic]

108
00:07:19,910 --> 00:07:22,130
Huh? That silence, could it be...

109
00:07:22,130 --> 00:07:23,600
You quit your affair?

110
00:07:23,600 --> 00:07:25,200
Not so blunt, Akina!

111
00:07:26,050 --> 00:07:29,350
He's been busy. I haven't seen him recently.

112
00:07:29,350 --> 00:07:33,460
You must be feeling so lonely.

113
00:07:33,970 --> 00:07:37,010
But that'll make your reunion
all the more invigorating.

114
00:07:37,010 --> 00:07:38,340
I guess that's not a bad deal.

115
00:07:38,340 --> 00:07:40,950
You never change, Akina.

116
00:07:50,440 --> 00:07:53,920
<i>Can we meet in the next couple weeks?</i>

117
00:08:06,780 --> 00:08:10,850
I need to tell you something.

118
00:08:11,550 --> 00:08:13,250
What's up?

119
00:08:14,210 --> 00:08:17,230
I went to the clinic the other day.

120
00:08:21,030 --> 00:08:24,560
They say my uterine fibroids
are growing larger.

121
00:08:26,500 --> 00:08:28,600
Uterine fibroids?

122
00:08:30,460 --> 00:08:35,220
I've been suppressing them with medication
for the last couple years.

123
00:08:35,850 --> 00:08:38,740
They're expanding quite a bit,

124
00:08:38,740 --> 00:08:42,330
so the doctor said
I ought to consider surgery.

125
00:08:42,920 --> 00:08:44,980
Surgery...

126
00:08:46,420 --> 00:08:49,210
There are many types of procedures now.

127
00:08:49,210 --> 00:08:52,480
They won't have to cut an incision
in my body for this one.

128
00:08:54,960 --> 00:08:57,400
Then that's fine, right?

129
00:08:57,400 --> 00:08:58,720
What?

130
00:08:58,720 --> 00:09:01,580
Your health is my utmost priority.

131
00:09:02,610 --> 00:09:06,920
Besides, one child is enough for us.

132
00:09:13,470 --> 00:09:15,720
Enough?

133
00:09:23,700 --> 00:09:25,700
What do you mean, "enough"?

134
00:09:25,700 --> 00:09:28,210
"Enough"?

135
00:09:28,210 --> 00:09:29,970
Why is that your decision to make?

136
00:09:29,970 --> 00:09:33,510
It's my body, my life.

137
00:09:33,510 --> 00:09:37,210
Why is he always so condescending with me?

138
00:10:20,500 --> 00:10:23,100
I missed you!

139
00:10:31,230 --> 00:10:35,410
Fuyumi, you've been avoiding me.

140
00:10:35,410 --> 00:10:37,540
Well, I...

141
00:10:41,390 --> 00:10:43,450
Have you had enough of this?

142
00:10:44,990 --> 00:10:46,780
Of me?

143
00:10:46,780 --> 00:10:48,830
No, of course not.

144
00:10:48,830 --> 00:10:50,970
Then are you scared?

145
00:10:53,930 --> 00:10:56,120
Well...

146
00:11:01,160 --> 00:11:03,200
So am I.

147
00:11:04,760 --> 00:11:07,250
If we're found out, it's all over.

148
00:11:13,880 --> 00:11:17,240
But I'm more terrified of losing you.

149
00:11:20,170 --> 00:11:24,390
Are you free next Thursday?

150
00:11:24,390 --> 00:11:27,260
I have the day off for once,

151
00:11:27,260 --> 00:11:29,230
and I want us to talk.

152
00:11:30,600 --> 00:11:33,940
[Operation Date: February 27th, Friday]

153
00:11:35,860 --> 00:11:37,390
Thursday is...

154
00:11:37,390 --> 00:11:38,880
I'm free all day.

155
00:11:38,880 --> 00:11:41,580
Visit me after work,
in the morning, whenever.

156
00:11:43,150 --> 00:11:44,830
Sorry, I'll be busy.

157
00:11:44,830 --> 00:11:46,630
Then how about Friday night?

158
00:11:46,630 --> 00:11:49,400
I should wrap up early that day.

159
00:11:50,230 --> 00:11:52,990
I can't do Friday, either.

160
00:11:59,840 --> 00:12:01,780
I guess...

161
00:12:03,750 --> 00:12:08,020
This is it for us then?

162
00:12:08,660 --> 00:12:10,140
No, that's not it.

163
00:12:10,140 --> 00:12:14,070
I have surgery on Friday,
and since Thursday is the day before, I...

164
00:12:14,070 --> 00:12:15,770
Surgery?

165
00:12:16,880 --> 00:12:18,570
Fuyumi, is everything okay?

166
00:12:18,570 --> 00:12:20,040
Are you ill?

167
00:12:20,040 --> 00:12:22,970
Do you need to sit?
Wait, there're no benches around.

168
00:12:22,970 --> 00:12:24,540
Here, use my jacket.

169
00:12:24,540 --> 00:12:28,520
No, it's really no big deal.

170
00:12:28,520 --> 00:12:32,030
- But...
- I need to get some uterine growth removed.

171
00:12:32,030 --> 00:12:34,910
The procedure ends in an hour,
and I'm only bedridden a few days.

172
00:12:34,910 --> 00:12:36,660
So really, it's no big deal...

173
00:12:36,660 --> 00:12:39,070
It is a big deal.

174
00:12:44,520 --> 00:12:48,690
It is a big deal, isn't it?

175
00:12:57,910 --> 00:12:59,640
I'm sorry.

176
00:13:00,960 --> 00:13:05,280
I'm sorry I never noticed.

177
00:13:08,220 --> 00:13:10,480
You must be so anxious.

178
00:13:12,040 --> 00:13:14,140
You must be terrified.

179
00:13:15,680 --> 00:13:20,360
What can I do to help?

180
00:13:38,160 --> 00:13:39,280
10,000 copies?

181
00:13:39,280 --> 00:13:41,810
Yes, for the first print.

182
00:13:41,810 --> 00:13:43,010
Really?

183
00:13:43,010 --> 00:13:45,020
That's a bit much...

184
00:13:45,020 --> 00:13:47,140
Don't worry about the numbers.

185
00:13:47,140 --> 00:13:51,090
Shibuya will design a book cover that sells.

186
00:13:51,090 --> 00:13:53,830
That's a lot of pressure
for a vague order, boss.

187
00:13:53,830 --> 00:13:56,500
And Haru,
you'll write an exclusive short story.

188
00:13:56,500 --> 00:13:58,650
- 100 pages will suffice.
- 100?

189
00:13:58,650 --> 00:14:00,720
To incentivize people to buy your book.

190
00:14:00,720 --> 00:14:04,260
The main story is only 120 pages.
You want me to double that?

191
00:14:04,260 --> 00:14:07,110
Yes. Good luck!

192
00:14:11,200 --> 00:14:14,610
Will you be able to manage
an extra 100 pages?

193
00:14:14,610 --> 00:14:17,190
I'll have to.

194
00:14:17,960 --> 00:14:20,540
I can't let this opportunity go to waste.

195
00:14:22,610 --> 00:14:25,330
Haru, you've changed.

196
00:14:25,330 --> 00:14:26,670
Huh?

197
00:14:26,670 --> 00:14:28,540
You've become beautiful.

198
00:14:34,730 --> 00:14:36,480
You think?

199
00:14:36,480 --> 00:14:38,060
Yes, you have.

200
00:14:53,140 --> 00:14:56,540
[That night has changed things
for the better.]

201
00:15:10,490 --> 00:15:13,390
Nail clippers...

202
00:15:13,390 --> 00:15:15,510
Nail clippers...

203
00:15:15,510 --> 00:15:17,350
Where did I put them?

204
00:15:38,080 --> 00:15:42,060
<i>Toss your old condoms, and use these instead.</i>

205
00:15:42,060 --> 00:15:45,210
<i>With your husband, another dude, or...</i>

206
00:15:48,170 --> 00:15:50,160
<i>You've become beautiful.</i>

207
00:15:50,940 --> 00:15:54,400
No, absolutely not.

208
00:16:09,110 --> 00:16:11,220
I'm home.

209
00:16:16,060 --> 00:16:18,290
Welcome back.

210
00:16:18,290 --> 00:16:20,650
- You're early.
- Yeah.

211
00:16:20,650 --> 00:16:23,940
The guys from the record label
wanted to grab dinner,

212
00:16:23,940 --> 00:16:26,530
so I let Suzuki and Tanaka handle that.

213
00:16:26,530 --> 00:16:28,550
You didn't need to join them?

214
00:16:28,550 --> 00:16:31,440
Nah, it was a sudden invite anyway.

215
00:16:33,300 --> 00:16:34,960
I'm beat.

216
00:16:34,960 --> 00:16:36,410
Want something to drink?

217
00:16:36,410 --> 00:16:38,400
Wait, you didn't have dinner.

218
00:16:38,400 --> 00:16:41,050
- I'll whip up something for you.
- Haru.

219
00:16:44,580 --> 00:16:47,200
We can order something for us.

220
00:16:59,640 --> 00:17:01,580
Have you given it any thought?

221
00:17:01,580 --> 00:17:04,460
- Huh?
- Where you want to go for our outing.

222
00:17:06,580 --> 00:17:09,760
How about a hot springs day trip?

223
00:17:09,760 --> 00:17:11,720
Huh? A hot spring?

224
00:17:11,720 --> 00:17:13,560
What? Would you rather not?

225
00:17:13,560 --> 00:17:16,920
No, that's not it, but...

226
00:17:16,920 --> 00:17:19,260
Then where do you want to go?

227
00:17:19,260 --> 00:17:21,900
- Erm...
- Five.

228
00:17:21,900 --> 00:17:23,360
Four.

229
00:17:23,360 --> 00:17:25,140
- Three.
- Hold on!

230
00:17:25,140 --> 00:17:26,970
Two.

231
00:17:26,970 --> 00:17:29,240
- One.
- I know!

232
00:17:36,620 --> 00:17:38,220
Wow!

233
00:17:38,220 --> 00:17:40,000
They actually ate it!

234
00:17:40,000 --> 00:17:43,440
<i>A zoo? How old are you?</i>

235
00:17:43,440 --> 00:17:46,600
<i>Zoos are always great for a date.</i>

236
00:17:46,600 --> 00:17:48,270
<i>A date, is it?</i>

237
00:17:48,270 --> 00:17:51,860
<i>That's what an outing
between a couple is called.</i>

238
00:17:51,860 --> 00:17:53,940
- Wow!
- Woah.

239
00:17:53,940 --> 00:17:55,570
It came here!

240
00:17:55,570 --> 00:17:59,260
Wow, it's so regal.

241
00:17:59,260 --> 00:18:02,020
And big, too!

242
00:18:06,100 --> 00:18:07,760
I played my heart out.

243
00:18:07,800 --> 00:18:11,400
Same. I can't believe I'm already worn out.

244
00:18:12,270 --> 00:18:15,850
Thanks. I had fun today.

245
00:18:16,530 --> 00:18:18,500
Glad to hear it.

246
00:18:30,850 --> 00:18:34,810
The boys and I are taking a trip next week,
before our concert.

247
00:18:34,810 --> 00:18:36,550
Three days, two nights.

248
00:18:36,550 --> 00:18:38,680
Really? That's so nostalgic.

249
00:18:38,680 --> 00:18:40,730
I remember all your old band trips.

250
00:18:40,730 --> 00:18:43,480
And I remember you'd always want to follow.

251
00:18:43,480 --> 00:18:45,410
Promising you'd be helpful to have around.

252
00:18:45,410 --> 00:18:48,200
I never did get to join one though.

253
00:18:50,360 --> 00:18:53,130
Want to come along for once?

254
00:18:53,840 --> 00:18:55,230
Huh?

255
00:18:55,230 --> 00:18:56,990
The other two wouldn't mind.

256
00:18:56,990 --> 00:19:00,130
They really seem to like you.

257
00:19:00,130 --> 00:19:02,200
How'd you do that?

258
00:19:02,200 --> 00:19:05,720
By changing you for the better?

259
00:19:06,700 --> 00:19:08,990
You're not wrong there.

260
00:19:13,910 --> 00:19:17,340
But I guess you'd have work, huh?

261
00:19:19,780 --> 00:19:24,930
Yeah. I'd join if I didn't have
deadlines coming up.

262
00:19:27,520 --> 00:19:29,430
Too bad.

263
00:19:46,190 --> 00:19:47,670
I'm so tired.

264
00:19:48,810 --> 00:19:50,390
Here's a coffee.

265
00:19:50,390 --> 00:19:52,030
Thanks.

266
00:19:53,070 --> 00:19:54,220
See you when I get back.

267
00:19:54,220 --> 00:19:56,450
Take care, and good luck.

268
00:19:56,450 --> 00:19:57,860
Thanks.

269
00:20:07,960 --> 00:20:10,930
Guess I'll get writing, too.

270
00:20:10,930 --> 00:20:14,490
[That night has changed things
for the better.]

271
00:20:22,630 --> 00:20:26,560
<i>That night has changed things for the better.</i>

272
00:20:27,590 --> 00:20:33,310
<i>Though my husband would not even kiss me,
I was desperate to love him,</i>

273
00:20:33,310 --> 00:20:35,820
<i>both in body and heart.</i>

274
00:20:36,720 --> 00:20:39,540
<i>But my desperation
could not be attributed to effort.</i>

275
00:20:39,540 --> 00:20:42,000
<i>No, that was an obsession.</i>

276
00:20:44,300 --> 00:20:47,430
<i>Once I cut my body from the equation,</i>

277
00:20:47,430 --> 00:20:50,870
<i>our cogs were set in motion once more.</i>

278
00:21:00,950 --> 00:21:02,470
<i>And yet...</i>

279
00:21:06,300 --> 00:21:08,480
"Yet"?

280
00:21:11,990 --> 00:21:14,240
"Yet", what?

281
00:21:19,620 --> 00:21:22,720
I'm getting hungry.

282
00:21:22,720 --> 00:21:25,010
Maybe I'll order delivery.

283
00:21:52,820 --> 00:21:54,970
<i>Or me, if you want.</i>

284
00:22:32,600 --> 00:22:34,040
<i>And yet...</i>

285
00:22:36,120 --> 00:22:38,850
<i>Life is not so simple.</i>

286
00:22:38,850 --> 00:22:44,100
<i>For once you've opened a door,
you crave to see what lies beyond it.</i>

287
00:22:48,320 --> 00:22:50,810
What the heck am I even writing?

288
00:22:54,450 --> 00:22:55,930
That was quick.

289
00:24:39,000 --> 00:24:58,600
[Preview]

